From: Manish Chopra <manish.chopra@qlogic.com>
Date: Thu, 15 Aug 2013 08:29:29 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 094/270] qlcnic: Fix diagnostic interrupt test for 83xx
 adapters
Patch-mainline: v3.11-rc6
Git-commit: d1fcc172570fa4de69c60bdabe1e1ccfcfe80c26
References: bsc#909350 FATE#317546

o Do not allow interrupt test when adapter is resetting.

Signed-off-by: Manish Chopra <manish.chopra@qlogic.com>
Signed-off-by: Sucheta Chakraborty <sucheta.chakraborty@qlogic.com>
Signed-off-by: David S. Miller <davem@davemloft.net>
Acked-by: Shahed Shaikh <shahed.shaikh@qlogic.com>
Acked-by: Gary Ching-Pang Lin <glin@suse.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qlcnic/qlcnic_83xx_hw.c |    5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qlcnic/qlcnic_83xx_hw.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/qlogic/qlcnic/qlcnic_83xx_hw.c
@@ -3274,6 +3274,11 @@ int qlcnic_83xx_interrupt_test(struct ne
 	u8 val;
 	int ret, max_sds_rings = adapter->max_sds_rings;
 
+	if (test_bit(__QLCNIC_RESETTING, &adapter->state)) {
+		netdev_info(netdev, "Device is resetting\n");
+		return -EBUSY;
+	}
+
 	if (qlcnic_get_diag_lock(adapter)) {
 		netdev_info(netdev, "Device in diagnostics mode\n");
 		return -EBUSY;
